The parents of two young children who were allegedly stabbed to death by their nanny in their Upper West Side apartment last year have revealed they are expecting a baby boy.

Marina and Kevin Krim shared the happy news on a Facebook page set up in the memory of their two slain children, two-year-old Leo and six-year-old Lulu.

The baby boy will join the Krims' surviving daughter, four-year-old Nessie, and will be born almost a year after the horrific murders last October.

